you navigate on this page below.<p><a href="#Anchor0">Whats New? section</a><p><a href="#Anchor1">TWMC club - very brief introduction</a><p><a href="#Anchor2">Table of events - where we have gone and where wewill be going</a><p><a href="#Anchor3">Meetings of TWMC - time, place and agenda of nextmeetings</a><p><a href="#Anchor4">Links to personal photo pages containing images ofwhere we have been</a></td></tr></table><p><hr><p><a NAME="Anchor0"></a><b><font size=+1>WHATS NEW?</font></b><p>This area gives brief details of changes to the web site, where andwhen to help update your information about the club.<p><b>Date</b><p>98/09/20 - Revision of homepage and small design changes<p>98/10/13 - Revision of homepage (changes to schedule and contacts),added <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/hakone.htm">Hakoneinformation</a><p>98/10/19 - Revision of homepage (changes to schedule), added<a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/yatsu.htm">Yatsugatakeinformation</a> and <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/north_alps1.htm">NorthAlps</a> link. Also, the proposed <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/guidelines.htm">TWMCguidelines</a> are for everyone to view and <a href="mailto:john.payne@kyowa.co.jp">comment</a>on.<p>98/10/20 - Addition of links to <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/oze1.htm">Oze</a>,<a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/fuji1.htm">Fujitrip 1</a>, <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/fuji2.htm">Fujitrip 2</a>, <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/kamakura.htm">Kamakura</a>,<a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/north_alps1.htm">NorthAlps</a>, and <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/south_alps1.htm">SouthAlps</a>. Most of these links have links to pictures or include some pictureswith addition of descriptions of the walks and some slanderous accusationsfrom Victor...<p>98/10/21 - Buying or loooking for gear? Well, before you buy, take alook at the updated web pages on <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/page3.htm">hikingadvice</a> where there are links to choosing / help on <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/boots.htm">walkingboots</a> , <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/rucksack.htm">rucksacks</a>, <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/sleepbag.htm">sleepingbags and mats</a> , and <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/tent.htm">tents(help on buying, variety, maintenance, pitching, and care of them)</a>.<p><b>98/11/05</b> - Want to know where we are going walking in the future,or where we have been? <a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/map_page.htm">Thentry the new MAP PAGE which allows some degree of interaction in searchingJapan</a> (all maps (C) <a href="http://www.mapple.co.jp/">Shobunsha Publications,Inc. from "Road Atlas Japan"</a>. The TWMC would like to thank <a href="http://www.mapple.co.jp/">Shobunsha</a>for their kindness in allowing these images to be used.). If you have acar or want to find out where places are in Japan, the "Road Atlas Japan"is the BEST map to buy - most place names in Kanji and Romaji (so usefulfor nihonji and gaikokujin!) and always up-to-date. We recommend you tobuy it (about 2500 yen).<p><hr><p><a NAME="Anchor1"></a><b><font size=+1>TWMC - very brief introduction</font></b><p>This is a new club - the <b><font color="#0033FF">Tsukuba Walking andMountaineering Club</font></b>, formed in May 1998. We decided to formthe club as many people (Japanese and <i>gaikokujin</i>) expressed thewish to go walking in Japan, including us, and so we decided to do somethingabout it and organise walks for everyone where we would like to visit asmany wonderful places as possible in Japan. We try and do walks for everyoneand all standards of walking. Join us and see. You couldn`t meet a morefriendly bunch of people... We are also known as the Tsukuba Walking andOnsen Club from time to time as we do try to find an onsen whenever wecan!<p><hr><p><a NAME="Anchor2"></a><b><font color="#000000"><font size=+1>The nextwalk is - see table below:</font></font></b><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<table BORDER=0 BGCOLOR="#CCFFCC" ><tr><td WIDTH="150"><b><font size=+3>DATE</font></b></td><td WIDTH="350"><b><font size=+3>WHERE </font><font size=+1>+ (deadlinefor booking)</font></b></td><td WIDTH="120"><b><font size=+2>CONTACT</font></b></td></tr><tr BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><td WIDTH="150"></td><td WIDTH="350"></td><td WIDTH="120"></td></tr><tr><td WIDTH="150"><b><u><font size=+2>June 1998</font></u></b></td><td WIDTH="350" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"></td><td WIDTH="120" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"></td></tr><tr><td WIDTH="150"><blockquote><b><font color="#000000"><font size=+1>7</font></font></b></blockquote></td><td WIDTH="350"><b><font color="#000000">Chiba-ken (Nokogiriyama)</font></b></td><td WIDTH="120">John Payne</td></tr><tr><td WIDTH="150"><blockquote><b><font color="#000000">20+21</font></b></blockquote></td><td WIDTH="350"><b><font color="#000000"><a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/oze1.htm">Oze</a></font></b></td><td WIDTH="120">Ichiko Tanabe</td></tr><tr BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><td WIDTH="150">&nbsp;</td><td WIDTH="350"></td><td WIDTH="120"></td></tr><tr><td WIDTH="150"><b><u><font size=+2>July</font></u></b></td><td NOWRAP WIDTH="350" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"></td><td WIDTH="120" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"></td></tr><tr><td WIDTH="150"><blockquote><b>5</b></blockquote></td><td WIDTH="350"><b><a href="http://www.geocities.com/Yosemite/Gorge/6108/old/kamakura.htm">Kamakura</a></b></td><td WIDTH="120">John Payne</td></tr><tr><td WIDTH="150"><blockquote><b>11 + 12</b></blockquote></td><td WIDTH="350"><b><a href="http://www.geoci